    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Published_LookupPublishedBillingPeriodLabels",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve and format billing period labels from a table named "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "MonthlyPublishedSummaryData",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Published",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema. It selects the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " column and formats it into a more readable label consisting of the month name and year. The results are ordered in descending order based on the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a simple "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SELECT",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " statement with basic string manipulation and ordering. It does not involve any complex logic, conditional statements, or joins."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "This stored procedure does not take any input parameters. It operates on the entire dataset available in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "MonthlyPublishedSummaryData",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Transaction Isolation Level",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure sets the transaction isolation level to "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", which allows reading uncommitted changes from other transactions. This is often used to avoid locking and improve performance at the risk of reading dirty data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Data Retrieval",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": It selects two columns:"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "bulletList",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "listItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": " is selected as "
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "[Text]",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "."
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "listItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "A formatted string is created as "
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "[Value]",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": ", which combines the month name (derived from the first two characters of "
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": " assumed to be in "
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "YYYYMM",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": " format) and the year (first four characters of "
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                          "marks": [
                            {
                              "type": "code"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "text": ")."
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Ordering",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The results are ordered by "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " in descending order, ensuring the most recent periods appear first."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This isolation level can improve performance by reducing locking overhead but at the cost of potentially reading uncommitted or dirty data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Indexing",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Performance can be improved if there is an index on the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " column, especially given the descending order requirement."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "String Manipulation",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The use of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "DATENAME",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SUBSTRING",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " functions for each row could have a minor impact on performance, but this is generally negligible unless the dataset is very large."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Dirty Reads",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Using "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " can lead to reading uncommitted data, which might not be suitable for all business scenarios, especially if data accuracy is critical."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Date Format Assumptions",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure assumes that "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "PublishedBillingPeriod",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is in a "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "YYYYMM",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " format. If this assumption is incorrect or if the data format changes, the procedure will produce incorrect results."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Lack of Parameters",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The absence of input parameters means the procedure retrieves all records, which might not be efficient if only a subset of data is needed."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "No Error Handling",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure lacks error handling, which means any runtime errors will not be gracefully managed or logged."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Overall, while the procedure is simple and efficient for its intended purpose, careful consideration should be given to the use of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and the assumptions about data format."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Stored Procedure Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CREATE PROCEDURE [Report].[usp_Published_LookupPublishedBillingPeriodLabels]\nAS\r\nBEGIN\r\n\tSET NOCOUNT ON;\r\n\tSET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL READ UNCOMMITTED;\r\n\r\n\tSELECT PublishedBillingPeriod AS [Text] \r\n\t\t,DATENAME(MM, PublishedBillingPeriod + '01') + ',' + SUBSTRING(PublishedBillingPeriod, 1, 4) AS [Value]\r\n\tFROM Published.MonthlyPublishedSummaryData\r\n\tORDER BY PublishedBillingPeriod DESC;\r\nEND;"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
